  <name>Break Escape SAFETYNET: Mission 1 — First Contact VMs</name>
  <author>Z. Cliffe Schreuders</author>
  <description>
# Break Escape SAFETYNET Mission 1: First Contact

Virtual machines for the Break Escape SAFETYNET mission 1 narrative experience. These VMs support the "First Contact" mission where operatives investigate Viral Dynamics Media to uncover ENTROPY's Operation Shatter disinformation campaign.

## Included Systems

**shatter_server** (172.16.0.2)
- Debian 12 desktop system
- Hosts ENTROPY infrastructure for Operation Shatter
- Contains accounts: derek (SSH brute force target), shatter (privilege escalation target)
- Intelligence: Archive decryption key, deployment notes, operation configuration

**kali** (172.16.0.3)
- Kali Linux penetration testing platform
- Used for reconnaissance and credential testing against shatter_server
- Includes Hydra for SSH brute force, standard penetration testing tools

## Integration with Break Escape

These VMs are provisioned by the Break Escape game engine via SecGen integration. Players interact with these systems through the game's narrative and task system, with guided hints delivered via SAFETYNET field guides.

## CyBOK Coverage

- Network Protocols and Vulnerability
- Penetration Testing Tools and Techniques
  </description>
  <lab_sheet_url>https://cliffe.github.io/HacktivityLabSheets/labs/m01_first_contact/safetynet-field-guide-ssh-access-and-linux-basics/</lab_sheet_url>
  <type>ctf-lab</type>
  <type>lab-sheet</type>
  <difficulty>easy</difficulty>

  <CyBOK KA="NS" topic="Network Protocols and Vulnerability">
    <keyword>common network attacks</keyword>
  </CyBOK>
  <CyBOK KA="SOIM" topic="PENETRATION TESTING">
    <keyword>PENETRATION TESTING - SOFTWARE TOOLS</keyword>
  </CyBOK>

  <system>
    <system_name>shatter_server</system_name>
    <base distro="Debian 12" type="desktop" name="KDE"/>

    <input into_datastore="IP_addresses">
      <!-- 0 desktop -->
      <value>172.16.0.2</value>
      <!-- 1 kali -->
      <value>172.16.0.3</value>
    </input>


    <!-- accounts on the desktop, with the main user as a normal user, a victim user with a crackable password (via ssh) with a flag and sudo access, and a bystander with a flag which the victim superuser can access via sudo -->
    <input into_datastore="user_accounts_desktop">
      <!-- main user, sudoer -->
      <generator type="account">
        <input into="username">
          <generator type="random_sanitised_word">
            <input into="wordlist">
              <value>mythical_creatures</value>
            </input>
          </generator>
        </input>
        <input into="password">
          <value>tiaspbiqe2r</value>
        </input>
        <input into="super_user">
          <value>false</value>
        </input>
      </generator>
      <!-- derek: ENTROPY cell operative, SSH brute force target, has sudo access -->
      <generator type="account">
        <input into="username">
          <value>derek</value>
        </input>
        <input into="password">
          <encoder type="string_selector">
            <input into="strings_to_encode">
              <value>Derek0419</value>
              <value>Derek_0419</value>
              <value>0419Derek</value>
              <value>April19Derek</value>
              <value>ViralDynamics</value>
              <value>ViralMedia2024</value>
              <value>Marketing2024</value>
              <value>Campaign2024</value>
              <value>SocialFabric2024</value>
              <value>Viral_Dynamics_Admin</value>
              <value>ViralAdmin0419</value>
              <value>OperationShatter</value>
              <value>OpShatter2024</value>
              <value>Entropy2024</value>
              <value>ZDS_Partner</value>
              <value>TrustIsLie</value>
              <value>VerifyEverything</value>
              <value>FilingCabinet0419</value>
              <value>Inevitable</value>
              <value>TheArchitect</value>
              <value>PatriciaKnew</value>
              <value>Misinformation</value>
              <value>NetworkSegment</value>
              <value>SafetyNet</value>
              <value>Derek_Marketing</value>
              <value>0419Marketing</value>
              <value>Architect0419</value>
            </input>
          </encoder>
        </input>
        <input into="super_user">
          <value>true</value>
        </input>
        <input into="leaked_filenames">
          <value>DECRYPTION_KEY</value> <!-- flag1: decryption key for the ENTROPY archive -->
          <value>operation_shatter/deployment_notes</value> <!-- flag2: directory traversal intel -->
        </input>
        <input into="strings_to_leak">
          <generator type="flag_generator" /> <!-- flag1: decryption key for the ENTROPY archive -->
          
          <encoder module_path="modules/encoders/selector/concatenate"> <!-- deployment_notes -->
            <input into="strings_to_encode">
              <value>OPERATION SHATTER -- DEPLOYMENT NOTES
Classification: ENTROPY CELL -- SOCIAL FABRIC
Operative: D. Lawson
Status: ACTIVE

The shatter account holds restricted operation files.
Use privileged access to read /home/shatter/ contents.
Archive credentials are stored in shatter's operation_shatter/ directory.

T-72 hours to launch.
-- The Architect</value>
              <generator type="flag_generator" /> <!-- flag2: directory traversal intel -->
            </input>
          </encoder>
        </input>
      </generator>
      <!-- shatter: ENTROPY infrastructure account, privilege escalation target, holds archive key -->
      <generator type="account">
        <input into="username">
          <value>shatter</value>
        </input>
        <input into="password">
          <generator type="strong_password_generator"/>
        </input>
        <input into="super_user">
          <value>false</value>
        </input>
        <input into="leaked_filenames">
          <value>launch_code/launch_flag</value> <!-- flag3: launch authorization code -->
          <value>shatter_configuration</value> <!-- flag4: encoded deployment intel -->
        </input>
        <input into="strings_to_leak">
          <generator type="flag_generator" /> <!-- flag3: launch authorization code -->
          <encoder module_path="modules/encoders/base/base64"> <!-- shatter_configuration -->
            <input into="strings_to_encode">
              <value>OPERATION SHATTER -- DEPLOYMENT CONFIGURATION
